DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Axillary Surgical Procedure Prior Surgery Present Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Information regarding a surgical procedure that occurred earlier in time that incises (opens) the armpit (axilla or axillary) to identify, examine, or remove lymph nodes inidicated by a yes/no response.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Breast Carcinoma Estrogen Receptor Status Progesterone Receptor Status Positive Finding Eligibility Determination Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A Yes/No/Not Applicable response regarding whether a carcinoma arising from the breast has estrogen receptor levels and progesterone receptor level measured in a primary tumor or in metastases is positive and  meets the requirements for enrollment into a clinical study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Metastatic And/Or Advanced Malignant Neoplasm Diagnosis Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A Yes/No/NA response regarding whether clinical or pathologic observation of a tumor extension from its original site of growth to another anatomic site has been observed OR abnormal cell activity manifested by decreased control over grown and function, causing excessive growth of benign or malignant tissue has occurred.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Absence of Signs or Symptoms Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown response to whether a person who is receiving medical attention, care or treatment or who is registered with medical professional or institution with the purpose to receive medical care when necessary has an absence of detectable signs or symptoms and meets the eligibility criteria for enrollment on a study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Bowel Obstruction Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A yes/no/not applicable response relating to information regarding a person having a tumor composed of atypical neoplastic which are relating to the fold of peritoneum, or mesentery, attached to the rectum as an element of a personal medical history which are necessary to allow an individual to participate in a specific clinical trial.

The yes/no/not applicable response to whether there is an existing hypersensitivity, a local or general reaction of an organism following contact with a specific allergen to which it has been previously exposed and to which it has become sensitized, to a therapeutic agent (drug, intervention therapy) used in a clinical trial protocol.
The yes/no/not applicable response relating to measurable or evaluable disease being present.
The response of yes/no/not applicable with regards to information relating to the patient's blood pressure (the pressure of the circulating blood against the walls of the blood vessels) determination

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Vital Signs Heart Rate Physical Examination Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/not applicable response regarding information relating to a physical examination (a systemic evaluation of the body and its functions using visual inspection, palpation, percussion, and auscultation, aimed to determine the presence or absence of physical signs of disease or abnormality for individual's health assessment) of a patient's heart rate (the number of heartbeats per unit of time, usually expressed as beats per minute).

The yes/no/not applicable information relating to the patient's respiratory rate (the rate of breathing (inhalation and exhalation) measured within in a unit time, usually expressed as breaths per minute) determination

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Vital Signs Temperature Physical Examination Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/not applicable response related to physical examination (a systemic evaluation of the body and its functions using visual inspection, palpation, percussion, and auscultation, aimed to determine the presence or absence of physical signs of disease or abnormality for individual's health assessment) of a person's body temperature.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Treatment Regimen Treatment Intent Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: information related to a prior treatment regimen._the description of a drug regimen or type of treatment given to a patient.
